        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-06-18 15:38:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nAndreas -\n\nThanks - The specific crash is client side only.  In the LU, Di pointed out I'd missed a change in master which fixes this in lmv_fld_lookup.  Sloppy on my part.\n\nI still feel like ll_fid2path should sanity check the FID it receives immediately (rather than pass it to the lower layers, which should perhaps assert rather than error), but since lmv_fld_lookup has been fixed, there is no need for this specific patch.\n\nIf you'd still like it as an improvement in ll_fid2path, I can fix and push it for that.  Otherwise I'll abandon it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
